Ondo command of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), has arrested no fewer than 150 hard drug suspects between January and June this year across the state. The command also in the same period, seized a total of 7, 702.114kg of hard drugs, comprising 7, 653.445kg of cannabis sativa, 48.669kg of psychotropic substances and 0.06grams of cocaine. The state Commander, Haruna Gagara, who made the disclosure in Akure , the state capital on Friday, noted that 138 of the suspects were males, while the remaining 12 were females. At the International Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit Trafficking with the theme: “Better Knowledge For Better Care,” Haruna emphasized that the need to mitigate the impact of drug abuse and illicit trafficking on the health and security of the citizenry. According to the NDLEA boss, “the current high rate of rape in the country, drug abuse is one of the predisposing factors fueling the rise in cases of this nature, therefore, the need for cooperation cannot be overemphasized. “if we must enjoy a drug free and healthy society devoid of crime, it is imperative that families, government, communities, non-governmental organizations, civil society organizations, religious organizations should take necessary steps to counter the rising drug problems in our country.” Haruna who disclosed that the cannabis sativa planters used government forest reserves to cultivate the illicit drug, noted that the development made it difficult for the agency to easily track them. He, therefore, solicited for the assistance of the public to inform the agency whenever the see such plantations anywhere, including forest reserves, while he emphasized on enlightenment programmes to discourage the youths from indulging in illicit drug consumption and trafficking.